# Plan Archiving & Status Tracking Rule

## Root Definition (Task Root)

- **Task root** = the root directory explicitly stated in the requirement (e.g. “以 `snake` 文件夹为根目录”).
- If the requirement does not specify a root, default to the workspace root.
- All paths in this rule are **relative to the task root**.

## Plan Location (Archive)

- Every execution must have a plan document archived at: `plan/plan.md` under the task root.
- If `plan/` does not exist, create it.

## Update Behavior (Real-time)

- When the plan is created or updated, **update the same `plan/plan.md` file** (do not create a new plan file per update unless user explicitly requests versioning).
- Keep `plan/plan.md` in sync during execution:
  - Mark items as **completed** as soon as they are done.
  - Keep remaining items clearly marked as **pending / not completed**.
  - If the approach changes, update the plan immediately to reflect the new steps and current progress.
  - Do not limit plan updates to only the beginning and end of the task.
  - For larger or parallel tasks, prefer assigning a dedicated subagent to maintain `plan/plan.md` while other subagents execute work.

## Requirement Changes

- If the user changes requirements (scope, acceptance criteria, deliverables), update `plan/plan.md` immediately:
  - Adjust goals/scope
  - Add/remove/rename steps
  - Update completion status to reflect the new plan

## Minimum Content Requirements

- Clear goal(s) / scope
- Step list with explicit status (completed vs pending)
- Use Markdown checkboxes in the step list: `- [ ]` and `- [x]`
- Notes on what was verified (if verification is part of the task)

